This paper deals with the convergence rates of deep neural networks, specifically in the context of unsupervised pretraining and dropout. These topics are closely related to machine learning and neural networks, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with the convergence rates of deep networks and learning mechanisms. The next likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with neural networks and their convergence rates. The paper also deals with topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI), which are also possible sub-categories.
